|WKO=====================================================================
|YKOKingdoms are player-ruled realms of Darkwind. Each kingdom has a Ruler,
a charter, a roster of citizens, its own nobility titles, and a heraldic
sigil carried by every citizen.

Founding: new kingdoms are chartered and activated with the help of the
game administration. If you dream of a throne, speak with the admins.

Joining: citizenship is by induction, in person. A noble with the power
to induct must stand in the same room as you and make the offer through
the kingdom's management menu. You are then asked whether you wish to
become a citizen; answer |YKByes|YKO or |YKBno|YKO. You must be at least
level 5 and cannot already belong to another kingdom.

Citizenship: you carry your kingdom's sigil, which cannot be dropped,
sold, or stolen, and it marks you as a citizen to anyone who looks at
you. You also gain the kingdom channel: |YKBkchat <message>|YKO speaks to
every citizen, and |YKBekchat <message>|YKO emotes to them.

Nobility: the Ruler may create custom titles, each granting any mix of
four powers: inducting members, removing members, assigning titles, and
owning a castle. New citizens start as "Citizen"; the title "Ruler" is
reserved for the kingdom's owner.

Management: the Ruler types |YKBmanagekingdom|YKO to hold court with the
Ministry of Administrative Affairs. Its sections are:

  Deeds And Titles         - set and view the charter, create, edit,
                             and remove titles, view citizens, induct
                             new members, bestow titles, and strip
                             citizenship.
  Heraldry And Propaganda  - name the sigil, choose its colors, and
                             write its descriptions.
  Castle Keep And Environs - the office of the Royal Engineer.

The whole kingdom hears arrivals and departures on the kingdom channel.|XX0

